item.name: SNMP Trap: RIPEX::trpNomadOffline
item.description:
A notification to indicate that Nomadic remote device is offline/online (i.e. status of connection to Nomadic base). This notification sends additional information about the event by including the following objects in its varbinding list. - alarmStateNomadOffline: alarm state.
Varbinds: 0. alarmStateNomadOffline (INTEGER) Alarm state - Nomadic remote offline.

item.name: SNMP Trap: RIPEX::trpUnitReady
item.description:
A notification to indicate that Unit ready signal has changed. This notification sends additional information about the event by including the following objects in its varbinding list. - alarmStateUnitReady: alarm input state.
Varbinds: 0. alarmStateUnitReady (INTEGER) Alarm state - Unit ready.

item.name: SNMP Trap: RIPEX::trpBpathAlt
item.description:
A notification to indicate a change in Backup paths system - alternative path state has changed. This notification sends additional information about the event by including the following objects in its varbinding list. - bpathsPeerIp: Backup path peer IP address. - bpathsName: Backup path symbolic name. - bpathsAltUsedPrio: Currently used alternative path priority number. - bpathsAltUsedGw: Currently used alternative path gateway IP address. - bpathsAltUsedState: Currently used alternative path state.
Varbinds: 0. bpathsPeerIp (OCTETSTR) Backup Paths - Peer IP address.
1. bpathsName (OCTETSTR) Backup Paths - Symbolic Name.
2. bpathsAltUsedPrio (INTEGER32) Backup Paths - Alternative Paths - Currently used path priority.
3. bpathsAltUsedGw (OCTETSTR) Backup Paths - Alternative Paths - Currently used path Gateway IP address.
4. bpathsAltUsedState (INTEGER) Backup Paths - Alternative Paths - Currently used path State.

item.name: SNMP Trap: RIPEX::trpBpath
item.description:
A notification to indicate a change in Backup paths system - backup path state has changed. This notification sends additional information about the event by including the following objects in its varbinding list. - bpathsPeerIp: Backup path peer IP address. - bpathsName: Backup path symbolic name. - bpathsAltUsedPrio: Currently used alternative path priority number. - bpathsAltUsedGw: Currently used alternative path gateway IP address. - bpathsAltUsedState: Currently used alternative path state.
Varbinds: 0. bpathsPeerIp (OCTETSTR) Backup Paths - Peer IP address.
1. bpathsName (OCTETSTR) Backup Paths - Symbolic Name.
2. bpathsAltUsedPrio (INTEGER32) Backup Paths - Alternative Paths - Currently used path priority.
3. bpathsAltUsedGw (OCTETSTR) Backup Paths - Alternative Paths - Currently used path Gateway IP address.
4. bpathsAltUsedState (INTEGER) Backup Paths - Alternative Paths - Currently used path State.

item.name: SNMP Trap: RIPEX::trpHotStby
item.description:
A notification to indicate that device in Hot Standby mode has been activated. This notification sends additional information about the event by including the following objects in its varbinding list. - serialNumber: Product serial number. - stationName: Station name.
Varbinds: 0. serialNumber (UNSIGNED32) Product serial number.
1. stationName (OCTETSTR) Station Name.

item.name: SNMP Trap: RIPEX::trpHwIn
item.description:
A notification to indicate that HW alarm input state has changed. This notification sends additional information about the event by including the following objects in its varbinding list. - ifHwAInputState: HW alarm input contact state. - ifHwAInputType: HW alarm input contact type.
Varbinds: 0. ifHwAInputState (INTEGER) HW alarm input contact state.

1. wvRxTxCom2 (INTEGER32) Local station - COM2 interface Rx to Tx packets ratio value from interval <1, 10000> in hundredths.
